To run an example of 1D random walk on a filament:
$ ecell3-session 1D.py

To view the simulation results wth the Spatiocyte Visualizer:
$ spatiocyte

To create a movie of the simulation results generated by matplotlib (requires avconv preinstalled):
$ python plot.py

We can use the VLC player to view the movie file:
$ vlc CoordinateLog.csv.mov 

To create high quality frames using Blender (warning, this will take a lot of computational time):
$ blender --background --python blender.py
Change the following lines in the blender.py file to increase resolution and quality:
  bpy.context.scene.render.resolution_percentage = 100
  bpy.context.scene.cycles.samples = 100

To create a movie of those frames:
$ avconv -i image%04d.png -vcodec qtrle blender.mov

To run an example of biased 1D random walk on a filament:
$ ecell3-session 1D_biased_walk.py
